<!--
    Thai (th) — translated from values-de/ (German source of truth).

    Script notes:
    • Thai script (อักษรไทย) is an abugida written left-to-right with no spaces
      between words. Android renders Thai via the bundled Noto Sans Thai font
      from API 21+; no extra configuration needed.
    • Thai uses no spaces between words, so word-wrapping is handled by the
      Android text engine's line-break algorithm (ICU), which correctly
      identifies Thai word boundaries. Do NOT add artificial spaces between
      Thai words — this would be incorrect and look wrong to native readers.
    • Register: polite formal (ราชาศัพท์ is too formal; standard written Thai
      uses ท่าน/คุณ + ครับ/ค่ะ particles; in UI strings the particles are
      omitted as per Thai app-UI convention, keeping strings gender-neutral).
    • "Binge drinking" → ดื่มแอลกอฮอล์มากเกินไป (public-health phrasing).
    • DHS is kept as "DHS"; WHO is written "WHO" (both used in Thai public health
      as foreign-organisation abbreviations).
    • day_change_time_value: Thai uses the same HH:MM 24-hour format; no suffix
      is needed (the German "Uhr" has no direct Thai equivalent in 24-h context).
    • Numbers: Thai has its own digit set (๐๑๒๓๔๕๖๗๘๙) but the international
      Arabic numerals (0–9) are standard in modern Thai UI/app contexts and are
      what Android's format strings (%1$d, %1$s) produce by default.
-->
